<br>
Fox was also smart by making sure all the female broadcasters are &quot;hot&quot;.  Thats nothing new when it comes to talking heads.  Even local stations tend to hire good looking female broadcasters.  Fox took it to a new level though.  Greta leaves CNN, gets plastic surgery, then starts working for Fox.  Main reason to watch Fox's coverage of the Iraq war was Jennifer Eccleston.  Hell if Playboy ever did a &quot;Woman of Fox News&quot; issue it would be one of their all-time best selling issues.  <br>
<br>
IMO, the criticism Fox News gets from the liberals is just another example of the ideological riftwar that has recently come to light.  Prior to Clinton, the Democrats and Republicans, while they disagreed with each other, at least showed respect to one another and tried to reach a compromise.  IMO this changed when Clinton became president.  That initiated the ideological war between liberals and conservatives.  Instead of respect, now we have constant negativity.  Each side tries to force their agenda down the others throat, compromise be damned.  This grew in magnitude when Bush Jr was elected.  Liberals feel the same towards Bush the way that conservatives felt towards Clinton.  Until a moderate gets elected, the ideological riftwar will just go back forth depending on what party controls the presidency.  <br>
<br>
Fox News took a side in this ideological riftwar.  As a result, the are reaping the financial rewards.  Criticize them all you want but I doubt they really care.  They will just laugh at you while their ratings continue to beat the competition. <p>Kebkin <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
